name: Ampharos
flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.
Ability1Text: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokemon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poke-Body each turn.
Attack1Text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Blastoise
flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach as many basic Water Energy cards from your hand to any of your Pokemon in any way you like. If you do, your turn ends. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It is said that CHARIZARD's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has 3 or less Prize cards left, each of Charizard's attacks does 50 more damage to the Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard. If tails, discard 4 Energy cards attached to Charizard. (If you can't, this attack does nothing.)

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Ability1Text: Whenever 1 of your opponent's Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from Entei's attacks, discard the top 3 cards from your opponent's deck.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Flip a coin. If tails, discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Entei.

name: Flygon
flavorText: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as "The Desert Spirit."
Ability1Text: As long as Flygon is your Active Pokemon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Active Pokemon between turns, excluding Fighting Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If you attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to Flygon during this turn, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Gallade
flavorText: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on the Defending Pokemon until it is 50 HP away from being Knocked Out. If you do, your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may choose as many of your face-down Prize cards as you like and put them face up. If you do, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Prize card you chose. (These cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: It will try to guard its trusted Trainer with its life. It has the ability to see the future.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your opponent's discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. (The Supporter card remains in your opponent's discard pile.) You can't use more than 1 Telepass Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, your opponent can't use any Poke-Powers on his or her Pokemon.

name: Gastrodon East Sea
flavorText: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Gastrodon West Sea in play, you may move up to 3 damage counters from Gastrodon East Sea to 1 of your Gastrodon West Sea.
Attack1Text: Does 80 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon East Sea.

name: Gastrodon West Sea
flavorText: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon West Sea. Then, remove 2 damage counters from Gastrodon West Sea.
Attack2Text: Put 1 damage counter on each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Ho-Oh
flavorText: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.
Ability1Text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Ho-Oh would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may flip a coin. If heads, Ho-Oh isn't discarded. Instead, remove all damage counters, Special Conditions, and other effects from Ho-Oh. Then, discard all cards attached to Ho-Oh (except for Energy cards). This counts as Ho-Oh being Knocked Out and your opponent takes a Prize card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of different types of basic Energy cards attached to Ho-Oh.

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.
Ability1Text: Whenever Jumpluff would be damaged by your opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Jumpluff by that attack.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. For each heads, this attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting to close to it will leave you soaked with drool.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. If you choose a Benched Pokemon, switch the Defending Pokemon with that Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to the Pokemon you chose. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, Lickilicky can't attack.

name: Ludicolo
flavorText: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.
Ability1Text: At any time between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Ludicolo.
Attack1Text: If you have a Stadium Card in play, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. If your opponent has a Stadium card in play, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon and return it to your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 120.

name: Mew
flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe MEW to be the ancestor of Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If you have less cards in your hand than your opponent, draw cards until you have the same number of cards as your opponent. (If you have more or the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does nothing.)
Attack2Text: Choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon in his or her discard pile. Re-creation copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Mew performs that attack.

name: Raikou
flavorText: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to Raikou, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard 3 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Lightning Energy card you discarded. Then, attach those Lightning Energy cards to 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Roserade
flavorText: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage and remove 3 damage counters from Roserade.

name: Salamence
flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changes, and wings grew out.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 basic Fire Energy cards or 2 basic Water Energy cards attached to Salamence. If you discarded 2 basic Fire Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to the Defending Pokemon. If you discarded 2 Basic Water Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (If you can't discard cards, this attack does nothing.)

name: Suicune
flavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Suicune from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your discard pile for up to 3 Water Pokemon, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Venusaur
flavorText: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokemon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose either Asleep, Burned, or Poisoned. The Defending Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition. This power can't be used if Venusaur is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 4 damage counters from Venusaur.

name: Absol
flavorText: It senses disasters coming and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.
Attack1Text: Choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it. If you discarded a Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium card, choose 1 more card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.
Attack2Text: If you played Absol from your hand during this turn, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 10.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you play Arcanine from your hand to evolve 1 of your Benched Pokemon, you may switch Arcanine with 1 of your Active Pokemon. If you do, you may move any number of Energy cards attached to that Pokemon to Arcanine.
Attack1Text: Arcanine does 40 damage to itself.

name: Banette
flavorText: A doll that became a Pokemon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.
Attack1Text: Put as many damage counters as you like on Banette. (You can't put more than Banette's remaining HP.) Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If Banette is in your discard pile, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage, then search your discard pile for Banette, show it to your opponent, and shuffle it into your deck.

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: Its three heads moves alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Dugtrio during your opponent's next turn. If Dugtrio is your Active Pokemon at the end of your opponent's next turn, put 6 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.

name: Electivire
flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Electivire. This power can't be used if Electivire is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Discard all Lightning Energy attached to Electivire. Flip a coin for each Lightning Energy you discarded. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if Electrode would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may use this power. Electrode isn't discarded. Instead, attach it as an Energy card to 1 of your Pokemon. While attached, this card is a Special Energy card and provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Has no effect other than providing Energy.)
Attack1Text: You may do 40 damage plus 60 more damage. If you do, Electrode does 100 damage to itself.

name: Furret
flavorText: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: You may switch Furret with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Furret as you like to the new Active Pokemon.

name: Golduck
flavorText: A Pokemon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokemon's attacks. That Pokemon can use only that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: You may do 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If you do, Golduck is now Confused.

name: Golem
flavorText: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can't harm it.
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: You may do 40 damage instead of 80 to the Defending Pokemon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Golem by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Jynx
flavorText: It cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.
Attack1Text: If Jynx was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Move 2 damage counters from Jynx to the Defending Pokemon. If Smoochum is anywhere under Jynx, move 4 damage counters instead.

name: Magmortar
flavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.
Ability1Text: When you attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to Magmortar, remove 2 damage counters from Magmortar.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the number of Fire Energy attached to Magmortar.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Minun
flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any Pokemon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may draw 2 cards. You can't use more than 1 Minus Charge Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Minun is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: If you have Plusle on your Bench, you may move an Energy card attached to Minun to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Mothim
flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 40 more damage.
Attack2Text: If Mothim has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 damage plus 40 more damage.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. Before doing damage, you may switch 1 of the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. The new Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Nidoqueen on your Bench. This attack does 60 damage plus 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Pidgeot
flavorText: By flapping its wings with all its might, PIDGEOT can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.
Attack1Text: If Pidgeot was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does the same amount of damage done to Pidgeot to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Plusle
flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. You can't use more than 1 Plus Charge Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Plusle is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: If you have Minun on your Bench, you may do 20 damage to any 1 Benched Pokemon instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."
Ability1Text: If Sharpedo is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Sharpedo is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon has 2 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. This attack damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.

name: Sunflora
flavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Grass Pokemon. You can't use more than 1 Grass Whistle Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Sunflora is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, Sunflora is now Confused.

name: Unown [S]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown S, Unown E, and Unown T on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Weavile
flavorText: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Each of your Active Pokemon's type is Darkness until the end of your turn. If that Pokemon is no longer your Active Pokemon, this effect ends.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Darkness Energy cards and attach them to any of your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 6 or more cards in his or her hand, discard a number of cards without looking until your opponent has 5 cards left in his or her hand.

name: Wormadam Plant Cloak
flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Ability1Text: If Wormadam Plant Cloak has 2 or more Grass Energy attached to it, Wormadam Plant Cloak gets +40 HP.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon has fewer remaining HP than Wormadam Plant Cloak, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Wormadam Sandy Cloak
flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, excluding damage, done to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage plus 10 damage for each Fighting Energy attached to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

name: Wormadam Trash Cloak
flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokemon's body. The cloak is never shed.
Ability1Text: If Wormadam Trash Cloak has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, any damage done to Wormadam Trash Cloak by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Wormadam Trash Cloak does 20 damage to itself.

name: Xatu
flavorText: This odd Pokemon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if Xatu is on your Bench, you may choose 1 Special Condition from 1 of your Active Pokemon and remove that Special Condition. Then, 1 of the Defending Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition that you chose.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Breloom
flavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.
Attack1Text: Remove from Breloom a number of damage counters equal to the amount of Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon's Retreat Cost is 0, this attack does 60 damage plus 60 more damage.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: In the rocky mountains where CHARMELEON live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a Fire Energy attached to Charmeleon and this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Cloyster
flavorText: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Cloyster by attacks during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. For each heads, choose an opponent's Pokemon in play and this attack does 20 damage to those Pokemon. (You may choose the same Pokemon more than once.) (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Donphan
flavorText: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon, if any. You switch Donphan with 1 of your Benched Pokemon, if any.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 70 damage plus 60 more damage.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd's Leek Slap attack's base damage is 60.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd can't use Leek Slap.

name: Flaaffy
flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, Flaaffy does 10 damage to itself.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.
Attack1Text: Remove 1 damage counter from Ivysaur.

name: Kecleon
flavorText: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.
Ability1Text: If any basic Energy card attached to Kecleon is the same as the Attacking Pokemon's type, any damage done by attacks from the Pokemon to Kecleon is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does no damage to the Defending Pokemon. Instead, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kirlia
flavorText: It is highly perceptive of its Trainer's feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack. (The Supporter card remains in your discard pile.)
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Lombre
flavorText: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from his or her hand during his or her next turn.
Attack2Text: Remove 2 damage counters from Lombre.

name: Miltank
flavorText: It is said that kids who drink MILTANK's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, remove 3 damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Muk
flavorText: A toxic fluids seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.
Ability1Text: At the end of each player's turn, each of your opponent's Active Pokemon that has any Grass Energy attached to it is now Poisoned. If that Pokemon is already Poisoned, Toxic Sludge Poke-Body does nothing to that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused and can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, each of Nidorino's attacks does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Pidgeotto
flavorText: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Pinsir
flavorText: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack's base damage is 10 instead of 100.

name: Quagsire
flavorText: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river's bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Quagsire is your Active Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon has any Water Energy attached to it, you may remove 3 damage counters from Quagsire.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Raticate
flavorText: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: If Raticate has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Roselia
flavorText: ROSELIA raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Sableye
flavorText: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. Choose as many Trainer cards as you like, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If you and your opponent have a different number of Prize cards left, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Shelgon
flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, Shelgon's Protect Charge attack's base damage is 80.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Shelgon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Skiploom
flavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.
Ability1Text: If Skiploom has any Grass Energy attached to it, any damage done to Skiploom by attacks from your opponent's Evolved Pokemon is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Switch Skiploom with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Smeargle
flavorText: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. Trace copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Smeargle performs that attack.

name: Smoochum
flavorText: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Jynx from your hand onto Smoochum (this counts as evolving Smoochum) and remove all damage counters from Smoochum.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

name: Unown [K]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counters from 1 of the Defending Pokemon.

name: Unown [N]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown N, Unown O, and Unown D on your Bench, you may ask your opponent to take a Prize card. If he or she does, you take a Prize card. If he or she doesn't, draw a card.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Unown [O]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown O, Unown N, and Unown E on your Bench and you have 1 card left in your hand, you may draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Unown [X]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown X on your Bench, you may look at the top card of your opponent's deck and put it back on top of his or her deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Z]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Z is on your Bench and you have no cards in your deck, you may discard all cards attached to Unown Z and put Unown Z on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Remove as many damage counters as you like from each Unown you have in play. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Venomoth
flavorText: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.
Ability1Text: If Venomoth is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Venomoth is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Prevent all effects of an attack, excluding damage, done to Venomoth during your opponent's next turn.

name: Vibrava
flavorText: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
Attack1Text: Wartortle can't use Giant Wave during your next turn.

name: Bagon
flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Bagon.

name: Bulbasaur
flavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Burmy Plant Cloak
flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Plant Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard pile for a basic Grass Energy card and attach it to Burmy Plant Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Plant Cloak has any Grass Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Burmy Sandy Cloak
flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Sandy Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard for a basic Fighting Energy card and attach it to Burmy Sandy Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Sandy Cloak has any Fighting Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Burmy Trash Cloak
flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Trash Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard for a basic Metal Energy card and attach it to Burmy Trash Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Trash Cloak has any Metal Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Carvanha
flavorText: They can swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Clefairy
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Corsola
flavorText: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 different types of Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Diglett
flavorText: A Pokemon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.
Attack1Text: Draw a card from the bottom of your deck.

name: Duskull
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Half of all blackouts occur when this Pokemon appears at power plants and eats electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, Electabuzz does 30 damage to itself.

name: Grimer
flavorText: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: A Pokemon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Hoppip
flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when HOPPIP gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.
Ability1Text: If Hoppip has any Grass Energy attached to it, the Retreat Cost for Hoppip is 0.
Attack1Text: Remove all Special Conditions from Hoppip.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Lotad
flavorText: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokemon that can't swim.
Attack1Text: If Lotad has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Magmar
flavorText: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Mareep
flavorText: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Murkrow
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.

name: Natu
flavorText: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Phanpy
flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Phanpy.
Attack2Text: Phanpy does 10 damage to itself.

name: Pidgey
flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Psyduck
flavorText: If its usual headache worsens, its starts exhibiting odd powers. It can't remember doing so, however.
Attack1Text: If Psyduck is Confused, draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, Psyduck is now Confused.

name: Qwilfish
flavorText: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.
Ability1Text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Qwilfish is your Active Pokemon and is damage by an attack (even if Qwilfish is Knocked Out), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon between turns.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ralts
flavorText: It uses the thorns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Sentret
flavorText: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 2 cards of your deck, choose 1 of them, and put it into your hand. Put the other card on the bottom of your deck.

name: Shellder
flavorText: It swims backwards by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.
Attack1Text: Remove 2 damage counters from Shellder.

name: Shellos East Sea
flavorText: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 in any combination of Shellos West Sea and Shellos East Sea and put them on your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Shellos West Sea
flavorText: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.
Attack2Text: Discard a Water Energy attached to Shellos West Sea and remove all damage counters from Shellos West Sea.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Shuckle by your opponent's Pokemon that has any Special Energy cards attached to it.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. As long as the Defending Pokemon remains Poisoned by this attack, it can't use any Poke-Body.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Spinda
flavorText: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
Attack1Text: Draw a card from the top and the bottom of your deck.
Attack2Text: If any basic Energy card attached to Spinda is the same type as any Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to Squirtle. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

name: Stantler
flavorText: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon isn't an Evolved Pokemon, that Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Sunkern
flavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from Sunkern, search your deck for an Evolution card that evolves from Sunkern, and put it onto Sunkern. (This counts as evolving Sunkern.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Trapinch
flavorText: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
Attack1Text: Switch the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Venonat
flavorText: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At nights, its kind is drawn by light.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It looks just like a Poke Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.
Attack2Text: Voltorb does 50 damage to itself.

name: Wooper
flavorText: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Gardevoir LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), choose 1 of your Active Pokemon or 1 or your Benched Pokemon and switch Gardevoir with that Pokemon. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 Pokemon (yours or your opponent's) with the fewest remaining HP (excluding Gardevoir) and that Pokemon is now Knocked Out.

name: Honchkrow LV.X
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon would be Knocked Out by damage from this attack, you may search your discard pile for any 1 card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.
